        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston, S. C.</placeName>
                <date>Feb. 25. 1855</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev. Is. Leeser</addressee>,
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Dear Sir/    My sister-<lb/>in-law, <persName>Mrs. Jacob. I.
                    Moses</persName> having left for <placeName>N York</placeName>, you<lb/> will be
                kind enough to send the Occident again to her<lb/> direction, <placeName>419 Fourth
                    Str. New York</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Hoping that you will not be offended, I take<lb/> the liberty of
                calling your attention to a typographical error<lb/> in your version of the Bible,
                which I happened to find this<lb/> morning. It is in Deut. VIII, V. 17, where I
                read:<lb/> “the strength of <hi rend="underline">thy</hi> hand,” instead of “the
                strength<lb/> of <hi rend="underline">my</hi> hand,” <add>ועצם ידי</add>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">What do you think of <persName>Dr Wise's</persName> project with
                re-<lb/>gard to a “Conference.” Judging from the contents of<lb/> a letter which you
                wrote to me about 18 months ago,<lb/> you must <del>have</del> be in favor of it. Or
                have you changed<lb/> your opinion? Is it not worth <hi rend="underline">trying</hi>
                at least?</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Most respectfully,</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Dr M Mayer</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
